06/06/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Economy and Finance Minister George Alogoskoufis has described the reform of money losing state-run companies as a government priority. In an interview published in Sunday's (5 June) edition of Eleftheros Typos, Alogoskoufis added that efforts to streamline the public sector would focus particularly on ailing enterprises in public transport and the defence industry. (ANA - 05/06/05) 
